Although not a new description, this proposed new combination, as well as recent work pointing to past misidentification of species and genera in the Kosñipata valley (e.g., De la Riva et al. 2008 for the strabomantid frog
Psychrophrynella usurpator
) shows that much work remains to be done to gain a better understanding of anuran diversity in southeastern Peru .
